column69: Key West, Key West International Airport 3491 S Roosevelt Blvd
column153: Gravid female boa captured at Key West International Airport by Monroe County Sheriff's Office personnel. Snake was also reported on EDDMapS. The Key West Citizen (http://keysnews.com/node/42846) and Florida Keys Keynoter (http://www.keysnet.com/2012/10/12/482726/10-foot-python-found-at-key-west.html) newspapers reported that a large constrictor at the Key West Airport on Thursday, October 11, 2012. I have requested permission to attach (to this report) photos taken by Monroe County Sheriff's Office Sergeant Evan Calhoun; two were published (one in each) of the local newspapers cited in this record. The Key West Citizen published the snake's correct identification in a story by staff writer Adam Linhardt. The following is an excerpt from Linhardt's article as posted October 13 (2012) at http://keysnews.com/node/42846: A 10-foot boa constrictor captured by deputies and Key West International Airport authorities Thursday night most likely is a released or escaped pet and did not make its way to Key West from the Florida Everglades, officials said Friday. "This is a large red-tailed boa," Marathon veterinarian Doug Mader said Friday in an email to The Citizen. "It looks, in the photo, very healthy, so I suspect it is eating plenty." The boa constrictor was found at 6:30 p.m., right behind the terminal near a grassy area, said Monroe County Airports Director Peter Horton. Airport authorities turned the snake over to Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission (FWC) officers, Horton said." The Keynoter article (incorrectly) reported, both online and in their paper edition, that the snake was a python: "A 10-foot python -- a nonnative invasive species -- was found in the grass near the edge of the commercial ramp at Key West International Airport Thursday." As I post this report, I have not yet learned who has the snake, though newspapers reported that it was turned over to FWC officers (James G. Duquesnel, U. S. Geological Survey, personal communication).
